THE Johannesburg
Metropolitan Police Department (JMPD) Undercover Unit arrested five suspects
today for attacking their victims with knives. In the first incident
the Undercover Unit saw a male suspect stab a male victim in Banket Street
Hillbrow before 1am this morning. They arrested the
suspect and arranged for an ambulance to transport the victim in his late
twenties to Charlotte Maxeke Hospital,‚Äù Johannesburg Metropolitan Police
Department Spokesperson, Wayne Minnaar said. In the second incident
the Unit arrested four male suspects in Pretoria Street in Hillbrow for
stabbing a male victim and robbing him of his trousers, cellphone and takkies. Minnaar said this
victim was also taken to Charlotte Maxeke Hospital by ambulance.  